   public   boolean   equals ( Circle   circle )   { 
     System . out . println ( "equals(Circle) called" ); 
     return   (( circle . center . equals ( center )   &&   circle . radius   ==   radius ); 
   }   }    Since this new  equals()  method does not override the method in  Object , it gets its own slot in the method table of  Circle , instead of reusing one from the  Object .   Now, consider which version of  equals  are called by the following:   1
