A better situation to use inheritance is to model a IS-A relationship: when the subclass behaves just like parent class, but has some additional behaviors.  For instance, it is natural to model a  PaintedCircle  as a subclass of  Circle  -- since a PaintedCircle has all the behavior of  Circle , but has  additional  behaviors related to being painted.  1
