4 class   PaintedCircle   extends   Circle   { 
   Style   style ; 
     :  }    A more tricky situation for modeling a IS-A relationship occurs when the subclass behaves just like the parent class  most  of the time, but sometimes behave slightly differently than the parent.  Consider how we model a rectangle and a square.  Normally, we consider a square IS-A special case of a rectangle.  So, we could model as:   1
